{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"ghxk5d49n3245sgk2mn9fcm","title":"Utils","desc":"Some useful general-purpose tools and tricks","updated":1647649361698,"created":1647065346725,"custom":{},"fname":"linux.utils","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault","remote":{"type":"git","url":"git@github.com:ravila4/knowledgebase.git"}},"contentHash":"aa068f1b11cc93fea7c7fc1ca40f745a","links":[],"anchors":{"grep":{"type":"header","text":"grep","value":"grep","line":8,"column":0,"depth":2},"line-context":{"type":"header","text":"Line context","value":"line-context","line":10,"column":0,"depth":3},"inline-context":{"type":"header","text":"Inline context","value":"inline-context","line":18,"column":0,"depth":3},"curl":{"type":"header","text":"curl","value":"curl","line":26,"column":0,"depth":2},"piping-utils":{"type":"header","text":"Piping utils","value":"piping-utils","line":42,"column":0,"depth":2},"tee":{"type":"header","text":"Tee","value":"tee","line":44,"column":0,"depth":3},"sponge":{"type":"header","text":"Sponge","value":"sponge","line":65,"column":0,"depth":3}},"children":[],"parent":"77irrssbs1ld66im3uhw4yx","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"utils\">Utils<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#utils\"></a></h1>\n<h2 id=\"grep\">grep<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#grep\"></a></h2>\n<h3 id=\"line-context\">Line context<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#line-context\"></a></h3>\n<p>-A NUM\n: Print n lines of trailing context after each match.</p>\n<p>-B NUM\n: Print n lines of leading context before each match.</p>\n<h3 id=\"inline-context\">Inline context<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#inline-context\"></a></h3>\n<p>Limit the context to N characters before and after the match:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">grep</span> -o -E <span class=\"token string\">\".{0,10}wantedText.{0,10}\"</span> input_file\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"curl\">curl<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#curl\"></a></h2>\n<p>Pronounced \"See URL\". Curl is useful for sending HTTP/HTTPS requests.</p>\n<p>Common flags:</p>\n<p>-X\n: method. e.g. GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, etc.</p>\n<p>-H:\nheaders</p>\n<p>-d\ndocument to send in request body</p>\n<h2 id=\"piping-utils\">Piping utils<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#piping-utils\"></a></h2>\n<h3 id=\"tee\">Tee<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#tee\"></a></h3>\n<p>Named after a plumbing \"T\" junction, tee allows us to pipe the output of a command to be redirected to two different commands, or to an output file and the screen.</p>\n<p>Examples:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token comment\"># 1. redirect output to screen (stdout) and a file</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">ls</span> -la <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">tee</span> output.txt\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># 2. redirect output to a file and another command</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">ls</span> -la <span class=\"token operator\">|</span>  <span class=\"token function\">tee</span> output1.txt <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">head</span> \n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># 3. redirect output to two different files</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">ls</span> -la <span class=\"token operator\">|</span>  <span class=\"token function\">tee</span> output1.txt <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">awk</span> <span class=\"token string\">'{print $1}'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">></span> output2.txt\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># It can be useful for creating backup files</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">cat</span> myfile.txt <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">tee</span> myfile.bak <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> sed<span class=\"token punctuation\">..</span>.\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"sponge\">Sponge<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#sponge\"></a></h3>\n<p>Part of the <code>moreutils</code> package.</p>\n<p>Sponge delays a file's modification, by creating a temporary buffer that allows using the same file as both input and output of a pipe.</p>\n<p>For example:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">cat</span> myfile.txt <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">awk</span> <span class=\"token string\">'{print $1}'</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> myfile.txt\n</code></pre>\n<p>does not work, because \"myfile.txt\" gets overwritten before awk is finished processing it. The normal way around it is to write the output to a temporary file, then replace the original file with the temporary.</p>\n<p>On the other hand, we could use sponge:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">cat</span> myfile.txt <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">awk</span> <span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">`</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>print $1<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token variable\">`</span></span> <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> sponge <span class=\"token operator\">></span> myfile.txt\n</code></pre>","noteIndex":{"id":"i3e9kusp519n36iz1ioi387","title":"Ricardo's Notes","desc":"","updated":1660963919727,"created":1647055090448,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault","remote":{"type":"git","url":"git@github.com:ravila4/knowledgebase.git"}},"contentHash":"9cb227c82d046533deea61e24c8a1c1e","links":[],"anchors":{"welcome-to-my-personal-knowledge-base":{"type":"header","text":"Welcome to my Personal K